import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['home_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['home_score'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Score: {:.2f}'.format(data['home_score'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores across all games?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.histplot(data=data, x='score_diff', kde=True, color='blue')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('team').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='team', y='count', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of games played by each team?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    df = data.groupby('division').count().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='division', y='count', data=df)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of games played in each division?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
